Net-MAC version 1.2
====================

Net::MAC is a Perl module for dealing with MAC (Media Access Control) 
addresses, most frequently encountered as Ethernet addresses.  For 
detailed information on the module, please use the perldoc program: 

  perldoc Net::MAC

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires Perl 5.6 or later.  It will probably work on earlier 
versions of Perl, but it has not been tested.  

